      "note": "Lit., \"thou shalt see [or \"behold\"] mankind drunk\", i.e., behaving as if they were drunk. The illusory, purely subjective character of this \"seeing\" - implied in the use of the singular form tara (\"thou shalt see\") after the plural \"you\" employed in the first clause of this verse - justifies the rendering \"it will seem to thee that ...\", etc."
